<br>
The country of Iraq is slightly more than twice the size of the State of Idaho.  That's not a small area, I hope you can see this.  We've occupied that country for about a month.  Are you honestly saying you believe we should have been able to thoroughly search a country that size for WMD's when we're still experiencing attacks from Saddam loyalists, and can't truly walk the streets and buildings of that country without being shot at?<br>
<br>
We gave that sick motherfucker 11 years to hide these things, and you're giving a month to find them, in a country we aren't familiar with?  He knew we were coming, and he knew what we were coming for.   He managed to scoot with more than 1 billion dollars in curency, and you're doubting he got viable weapons out of country too?<br>
<br>
What I'm failing to see in all of this is why the naysayers are losing sight of all these facts.  Want to wait a decade to do something about him, and then want IMMEDIATE answers after we finally do.  I can't understand that.  I'm ALL for finding the silver lining in the meantime, and getting his ass out of power is it.  I have zero doubts as to his guilt, and neither did the UN.  They DEMANDED cerain actions and imposed sanctions for failure to comply.  Saddam watched a million of his people die without flinching (thanks for the info Tapeworm), and finally someone decided enough was enough.<br>
<br>
That's how America acted.  Certain ends that came out of this DID justify the means in my mind, but the true justification has yet to be given time enough to bear fruit.  Sit back and wait, give them a fair amount of time to do their job.<br>
<br>
